  "title": "Video Producer #76051",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Real Estate</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Video Producer</strong></li><li>Working Location: Chinatown</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Mon – Fri, 9.00am – 6.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $3,400 + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Create and edit videos, including filming, editing, adding visual effects, colour grading, and sound design</li><li>Continue learning and improving filming, editing, and production skills</li><li>Meet all project deadlines and aim to finish tasks early when possible</li><li>Tell creative stories through video content</li><li>Use videography and video editing experience for various projects</li><li>Operate video equipment such as cameras, gimbals, studio lights, and green screens for both indoor and outdoor shoots</li><li>Find and use royalty-free music suitable for each project</li><li>Take on different production roles as needed</li><li>Work independently or as part of a team to deliver project goals</li><li>Represent the company professionally during shoots and when working with clients</li><li>Clean and maintain production assets and equipment</li><li>Anticipate and solve production issues when they arise</li><li>Record and edit video and sound, including organizing raw footage, editing, creating graphics, adding music or effects, and managing project files</li><li>Manage and organize the company’s video library</li><li>Manage sound and music resources</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor degree in Multimedia, Broadcasting, or related disciplines</li><li>Strong passion for video production and filmmaking</li><li>Skills in shooting, editing, and photography preferred</li><li>Experience using software like Premiere Pro, After Effects, Photoshop, Audacity, or similar</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#76051 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
